cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper is about single image super-resolution, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of neural networks and adversarial learning, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the preservation of image details and the gradual increase in image resolution, which are related to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
